task.summary:
Added method to allow the choice of card to the player;
Added method of wait to emulate game timing;
Small corrections to log messages

Refactoring: Extracted AI decision-making logic into a dedicated method
Created `getBestCaptureForCard()` and `getDiscardCardScore()` methods to evaluate the best capture or best discard for a given card;
Updated `chooseAiCard()` to use the new methods and reducing code duplication;
`bestCapture` is now determined in a cleaner and more structured way.

Implemented the rule where if an identical card is present on the table, it must be captured instead of other possible options; Improved AI decision-making by considering the identical card rule before selecting the card to play; Adjusted player capture choices to respect the identical card rule when applicable
Fixed an issue for the last-turn capture not scopa;
Small corrections to log messages

Implemented round-end scoring by updating `calculatePoints()` to correctly calculate and assign points
Added `calculateBestPrime()` method to compute best prime value based on the highest prime-value per suit;
Introduced new log messages of start round, end round and score details;
Renamed score update methods in `GameState` for better clarity;
Small corrections to log messages and comments.

Added multi-round game flow and improved game state management

- Introduced a static variable `winningScore` to define the victory threshold, allowing customization;
- Implemented `resetRound()` to properly clear game state before a new round starts;
- Moved round initialization logic from `startGame()` to a new method `initializeRound()` for better re-usability;
- Added a loop in `startGame()` that continues playing rounds until a player reaches the winning score;
- Renamed methods and adjusted log messages for better readability and debugging;
- Added new `clear` and `reset` methods in `GameState.java` to handle proper state resets after each round;
- Moved the game start test from `GameController.java` to `Main.java` for better separation of concerns and easier testing.

Refactored logging system and solved a Scanner error

- Moved all logging methods from GameController to a new GameLogger class for better separation of concerns and updated GameController to use GameLogger methods for all log-related operations;
- Replaced multiple Scanner instances with a single global Scanner (inputPlayer) and now it closed only at the end of the game to prevent NoSuchElementException errors;
- Removed try-with-resources and unnecessary scanner.close() calls inside methods;

Added winner announcement and rematch/quit option in endgame

- Implemented announceWinner() to display the final scores and declare the winner;
- Added playAgainOption() to allow the player to choose between replaying or exiting after the game ends;
- Updated startGame() to loop and reset the game state if the player chooses to play again;
- Added resetGame() method to reset the current game, including scores, to play a new game.

Added player name customization at game start

- Introduced an input prompt at the beginning of the game to set the player's name;
- Stored the player's name in GameState.

Added game start menu and randomized dealer selection
- Implemented a main menu in Main.java to allow the player to start the game or exit;
- Added the random card draw mechanic at game start to determine the dealer and which player begins;
- Added the drawCard by index method in Deck.java
- Updated logs to display the chosen name instead of a generic "PLAYER";

